cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the benefits of opportunistic routing in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves analyzing the power and delay scaling behavior, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The use of computer simulations suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), while the focus on improving the power-delay trade-off could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
